1
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:03,000
One of the biggest advantages of using WordPress is the ability to choose and install plugins

2
00:00:06,360 --> 00:00:09,360
to extend the functionality of your website.

3
00:00:09,440 --> 00:00:12,440
There are a variety of plugins available that can be used to add extra functionality around

4
00:00:14,280 --> 00:00:17,280
social media, analytics, security, marketing, membership and subscriptions, performance

5
00:00:20,040 --> 00:00:23,040
optimization, SEO and the list goes on.

6
00:00:23,440 --> 00:00:26,440
These plugins can help you get more out of your website and make it more dynamic.

7
00:00:29,040 --> 00:00:32,040
Maybe you would like to add a map, a contact form, to launch a multilingual website,

8
00:00:35,920 --> 00:00:38,920
build an e-commerce site or increase the speed of your site with caching.

9
00:00:41,080 --> 00:00:44,080
All of this can be achieved with the right plugins.

10
00:00:44,720 --> 00:00:47,720
You can view all the thousands of plugins available when you visit WordPress.org and

11
00:00:49,000 --> 00:00:52,000
browse through the Plugins Directory.

12
00:00:51,400 --> 00:00:54,400
While all of the plugins mentioned are free and available in the WordPress.org Plugin

13
00:00:55,280 --> 00:00:58,280
Repository, they may also have premium versions available at a cost that provide more functionality.

14
00:01:02,720 --> 00:01:05,720
To add a plugin, make your way to Plugins in the WordPress dashboard and select Add New.

15
00:01:08,600 --> 00:01:11,600
This will open up on the featured page and you have the option to view the most popular

16
00:01:13,120 --> 00:01:16,120
plugins, recommended plugins and a favourites tab.

17
00:01:17,920 --> 00:01:20,920
When you are ready to find a suitable plugin, use the search function at the top right of

18
00:01:22,120 --> 00:01:25,120
the page.

19
00:01:23,200 --> 00:01:26,200
If you type SEO for example, the repository gives you a list of plugins based on what

20
00:01:28,200 --> 00:01:31,200
you searched.

21
00:01:29,200 --> 00:01:32,200
Now, let's talk about what to look out for when choosing a plugin.

22
00:01:33,680 --> 00:01:36,680
Let's compare the three top plugins.

23
00:01:36,360 --> 00:01:39,360
There are four important things to take note of.

24
00:01:38,880 --> 00:01:41,880
Firstly the star rating.

25
00:01:40,560 --> 00:01:43,560
That refers to feedback from customers who installed the plugin.

26
00:01:44,000 --> 00:01:47,000
Secondly, when it was last updated.

27
00:01:46,760 --> 00:01:49,760
This indicates it is actively being supported and worked on.

28
00:01:50,200 --> 00:01:53,200
So I would suggest avoiding plugins that have not been updated in a long time.

29
00:01:55,080 --> 00:01:58,080
Thirdly, active installations.

30
00:01:58,000 --> 00:02:01,000
This indicates a popular and well supported plugin.

31
00:02:01,600 --> 00:02:04,600
And then lastly, compatibility.

32
00:02:03,840 --> 00:02:06,840
Make sure the plugin is compatible with the latest version of WordPress.

33
00:02:09,040 --> 00:02:12,040
When you click on more details, you will be able to see how well supported a plugin

34
00:02:13,200 --> 00:02:16,200
is.

35
00:02:14,200 --> 00:02:17,200
There is also an area for frequently asked questions and a place where you can read reviews.

36
00:02:20,160 --> 00:02:23,160
Let's search for a different plugin as an example of how to install and activate a plugin.

37
00:02:25,600 --> 00:02:28,600
We will go ahead and search for a forms plugin.

38
00:02:28,080 --> 00:02:31,080
There are various options for example Contact Form 7, Contact Form by WP forms and Ninja

39
00:02:33,840 --> 00:02:36,840
Forms.

40
00:02:34,840 --> 00:02:37,840
I will go ahead and install Contact Form by WP forms and once installed, you have to

41
00:02:40,640 --> 00:02:43,640
click on Activate.

42
00:02:42,880 --> 00:02:45,880
And then of course it's time to set up the plugin.

43
00:02:45,680 --> 00:02:48,680
And when your plugin is set up, it's a simple task using your block directory to add the

44
00:02:50,560 --> 00:02:53,560
form wherever you wish.

45
00:02:55,920 --> 00:02:58,920
Please note, you can also easily add a new plugin by uploading a zip archive of the

46
00:03:01,020 --> 00:03:04,020
plugin from your local computer.

47
00:03:03,560 --> 00:03:06,560
Many premium plugins can be downloaded outside the WordPress Plugin Directory.

48
00:03:08,480 --> 00:03:11,480
If you would like to stop using a plugin, you can go to your plugin section and click

49
00:03:12,640 --> 00:03:15,640
on Deactivate.

50
00:03:14,320 --> 00:03:17,320
And once deactivated, you will have the option to delete the plugin permanently.

51
00:03:23,920 --> 00:03:26,920
But what happens if you experience a plugin conflict?

52
00:03:27,920 --> 00:03:30,920
There are two main ways to identify plugin conflicts on your site.

53
00:03:31,800 --> 00:03:34,800
Number 1, manually deactivate plugins and then test them one by one to find the plugin

54
00:03:36,920 --> 00:03:39,920
causing a problem.

55
00:03:38,600 --> 00:03:41,600
And number 2, use a troubleshooting plugin, for example, Health Check and Troubleshooting.

56
00:03:45,520 --> 00:03:48,520
But remember to install well-built plugins and use the four criteria we discussed earlier.

57
00:03:51,640 --> 00:03:54,640
Plugins are amazing tools to add extra functionality to your site and I trust you will find the

58
00:03:55,920 --> 00:03:58,920
right ones to meet your needs.

